Docs.summary: Emits branches and exception blocks in a method body.

remarks.format:
## Remarks The <xref:System.Reflection.Metadata.Ecma335.ControlFlowBuilder> class is used to create branches and exception blocks in a method body encoded by <xref:System.Reflection.Metadata.Ecma335.InstructionEncoder>. For more information about emitting .NET assemblies, see the <xref:System.Reflection.Metadata.Ecma335.MetadataBuilder> class documentation.
## Examples This example shows how to emit a method body with the exception handler using <xref:System.Reflection.Metadata.Ecma335.ControlFlowBuilder>:
:::code language="csharp" source="~/snippets/csharp/System.Reflection.Metadata.Ecma335/ControlFlowBuilder/Overview/ControlFlowBuilderSnippets.cs" id="SnippetControlFlowBuilder":::
